  <h2>What Makes High Net Worth Divorce Different?</h2>
  <p>
    High-net-worth divorces differ from typical divorces in several critical ways:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Greater asset complexity:</strong> Multiple types of assets, many of which require expert valuation</li>
    <li><strong>Higher stakes:</strong> Errors in strategy or negotiation can result in catastrophic financial losses</li>
    <li><strong>Greater potential for hidden assets:</strong> Complex financial structures can conceal income and wealth</li>
    <li><strong>More sophisticated legal tactics:</strong> Opposing counsel in high-net-worth cases are typically experienced litigators</li>
    <li><strong>Prenuptial and postnuptial agreements:</strong> These may be contested and require careful analysis</li>
    <li><strong>Lifestyle and standard of living considerations:</strong> Spousal support in high-net-worth divorces can be substantial</li>
    <li><strong>Privacy concerns:</strong> Protecting financial information from public disclosure requires strategic case management</li>
  </ul>

