  <h2>Complex Assets We Handle</h2>

  <h3>Real Estate Portfolios</h3>
  <p>
    Multiple properties — primary residences, vacation homes, rental properties, commercial real estate, and investment properties — require individual appraisal and strategic division planning. Tax implications, rental income streams, mortgage obligations, and capital gains exposure are all factors in our analysis.
  </p>

  <h3>Investment Portfolios & Brokerage Accounts</h3>
  <p>
    Stocks, bonds, mutual funds, ETFs, private equity investments, hedge fund interests, and brokerage accounts accumulated during the marriage are subject to equitable distribution. We ensure accurate valuation dates, appropriate treatment of investment gains and losses, and tax-efficient distribution strategies.
  </p>

  <h3>Business Interests</h3>
  <p>
    Multiple business interests or significant ownership stakes require thorough business valuation by certified experts. We manage the entire process — from retaining valuators to challenging opposing expert opinions in litigation.
  </p>

  <h3>Retirement & Deferred Compensation</h3>
  <p>
    Executive retirement packages, defined benefit pensions, 401(k) plans, deferred compensation arrangements, and supplemental executive retirement plans (SERPs) all require careful analysis and, in many cases, QDROs or other specialized orders.
  </p>

  <h3>Trusts & Estate Planning Instruments</h3>
  <p>
    Inherited wealth held in trusts, family trusts, irrevocable life insurance trusts (ILITs), and other estate planning vehicles require analysis to determine what is marital versus separate property, and whether trust assets may be considered "available" for support purposes.
  </p>

  <h3>Cryptocurrency & Digital Assets</h3>
  <p>
    Digital assets — including cryptocurrency, NFTs, and digital investment accounts — are increasingly significant in high-net-worth divorce. Proper valuation and tracing of these assets requires specialized expertise that our attorneys are prepared to engage.
  </p>

  <h3>International Assets</h3>
  <p>
    Offshore accounts, foreign real estate, international business interests, and assets held in foreign jurisdictions add significant complexity. Our attorneys coordinate with international counsel when necessary to ensure comprehensive asset identification and division.
  </p>

  <h2>Prenuptial & Postnuptial Agreement Enforcement</h2>
  <p>
    High-net-worth divorces frequently involve prenuptial or postnuptial agreements. Whether you need to enforce an agreement that protects your separate wealth or challenge an agreement that is unfair or was improperly executed, our attorneys have the experience to handle these proceedings effectively.
  </p>

  <h2>Alimony in High Net Worth Divorce</h2>
  <p>
    When one spouse has significantly higher income and assets, spousal support can be a critical — and contentious — issue. Our attorneys conduct detailed lifestyle analysis, income capacity assessments, and financial projections to develop strategic alimony positions that protect your long-term financial interests.
  </p>

  <h2>Uncovering Hidden Assets</h2>
  <p>
    In high-net-worth divorces, asset concealment is a real and documented concern. Offshore accounts, underreported business income, manipulated cash flow, and undisclosed investment accounts are tactics our attorneys are trained to identify. We work with forensic accountants and financial investigators to ensure full financial disclosure and expose any attempts to conceal marital wealth.
  </p>

